{{infobox Chinese|l=Yin Metal Snake|kanji=辛巳|romaji=kanoto mi|onyomi=shinshi|p=xīnsì|w=hsin-ssu|mi=ɕin⁵³ sɨ|y=san1 si6|j=san1 si6|ci=sɐn siː|mc=sin si|oc-bs=sin slɯʔ}} {{出典の明記| date = 2021年6月}} {{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}
'''Kanotomi''' (辛巳) (pronounced ka-no-to-mi, shin-kin-no-mi, or shin-shi) is one of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}.
It is the 18th of the combined sets of the Ten Heavenly Stems and Twelve Earthly Branches. The one before it is {{ill|Kōshin (庚辰)|ja|庚辰}}, and the one after it is {{ill|Jingo (壬午)|ja|壬午}}. According to the {{ill|Yin-yang and Five Elements|ja|陰陽五行思想|lt=Yin-yang and Five Elements|lt_ja=陰陽五行}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|lt=Ten Heavenly Stems|ja|十干}} element {{ill|Kanoto (辛)|lt=Shin (辛)|ja|辛}} is the yin aspect of metal, and the {{ill|Twelve Earthly Branches|ja|十二支}} element {{ill|Mi (巳)|ja|巳}} is the yin aspect of fire. Under the concept of {{ill|Wu Xing#Mutual Restraint|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|lt=Mutual Restraint|lt_ja=相剋}}, fire subdues metal (火剋金).
== Year of Kanotomi (辛巳) ==
A Gregorian calendar year that, when divided by 60, has a remainder of 21 is a Kanotomi year. {| class="wikitable" |+'''Kanotomi Years''' |- !1st Millennium!!2nd Millennium!!3rd Millennium |- | *21 *81 *141 *201 *261 *321 *381 *441 *501 *561 *621 *681 *741 *801 *861 *921 *981 | *1041 *1101 *1161 *1221 *1281 *1341 *1401 *1461 *1521 *1581 *1641 *1701 *1761 *1821 *1881 *1941 | *2001 *2061 *2121 *2181 *2241 *2301 *2361 *2421 *2481 *2541 *2601 *2661 *2721 *2781 *2841 *2901 *2961 |}
== Month of Kanotomi (辛巳) == In the Gregorian calendar, during years ending in 0 or 5 (where the {{ill|Ten Heavenly Stems|ja|十干}} are {{ill|Kō (庚)|ja|庚}} or {{ill|Otsu (乙)|ja|乙}}), the fourth month (April) is the Kanotomi month. Note that this can refer to the month in the {{ill|Lunisolar calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Old Lunar Calendar}} or the “solar term” month (from {{ill|Rikka|ja|立夏}} to the day before {{ill|Bōshu|ja|芒種}}).
== Day of Kanotomi (辛巳) == A Kanotomi day is associated with the following selection day (選日).
=== Auspicious Days === On a Kanotomi day, it is the fourth day of {{ill|Small Earth|ja|犯土#小土|lt_ja=小土|lt=Shōdo}}.
