It is the 18th of the combined sets of the Ten Heavenly Stems and Twelve Earthly Branches. The one before it is {{ill|Kōshin (庚辰)|ja|庚辰|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, and the one after it is {{ill|Jingo (壬午)|ja|壬午|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. According to the {{ill|Yin-yang and Five Elements|ja|陰陽五行思想|lt=Yin-yang and Five Elements|lt_ja=陰陽五行|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|lt=Ten Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} element {{ill|Kanoto (辛)|lt=Shin (辛)|ja|辛|1=Kanoto (辛)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} is the yin aspect of metal, and the {{ill|Twelve Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} element {{ill|Mi (巳)|ja|巳|1=Snake (zodiac)|lt=Snake (巳)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} is the yin aspect of fire. Under the concept of {{ill|Wu Xing#Mutual Restraint|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|lt=Mutual Restraint|lt_ja=相剋|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, fire subdues metal (火剋金).
