{{infobox Chinese|l=Yin Metal Snake|kanji=辛巳|romaji=kanoto mi|onyomi=shinshi|p=xīnsì|w=hsin-ssu|mi=ɕin⁵³ sɨ|y=san1 si6|j=san1 si6|ci=sɐn siː|mc=sin si|oc-bs=sin slɯʔ|qq=}} {{出典の明記| date = 2021st year 6月|qq=}} {{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive|qq=}}
'''Kanotomi''' (辛巳) (pronounced ka-no-to-mi, shin-kin-no-mi, or shin-shi) is one of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|Sexagenary cycle comprehensive|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sexagenary cycle|qq=}}.
It is the 18th of the combined sets of the Ten Heavenly Stems and Twelve Earthly Branches. The one before it is {{ill|Kōshin (庚辰)|ja|1=Yang Metal Dragon|2=ja|庚辰|1=Yang Metal Dragon|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōshin (庚辰)|qq=}}, and the one after it is {{ill|Jingo (壬午)|ja|1=Yang Water Horse|2=ja|壬午|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jingo (壬午)|qq=}}. According to the {{ill|Yin-yang and Five Elements|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|lt=Yin-yang and Five Elements|lt_ja=陰陽五行|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-yang and Five Elements|qq=}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|lt=Ten Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Heavenly Stems|qq=}} element {{ill|Kanoto (辛)|lt=Shin (辛)|ja|辛|1=Kanoto (辛)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanoto (辛)|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanoto (辛)|qq=}} is the yin aspect of metal, and the {{ill|Twelve Earthly Branches|1=Earthly Branches|lt=Twelve Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Twelve Earthly Branches|13=User:Immanuelle/Earthly Branches|qq=}} element {{ill|Mi (巳)|ja|巳|1=Snake (zodiac)|lt=Snake (巳)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mi (巳)|13=User:Immanuelle/Snake (zodiac)|qq=}} is the yin aspect of fire. Under the concept of {{ill|Wu Xing#Mutual Restraint|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|lt=Mutual Restraint|lt_ja=相剋|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wu Xing#Mutual Restraint|qq=}}, fire subdues metal (火剋金).
== Year of Kanotomi (辛巳) == A Gregorian calendar year that, when divided by 60, has a remainder of 21 is a Kanotomi year. {| class="wikitable" |+'''Kanotomi Years''' |- !1st Millennium!!2nd Millennium!!3rd Millennium |- | *21 *81 *141 *201 *261 *321 *381 *441 *501 *561 *621 *681 *741 *801 *861 *921 *981 | *1041 *1101 *1161 *1221 *1281 *1341 *1401 *1461 *1521 *1581 *1641 *1701 *1761 *1821 *1881 *1941 | *2001 *2061 *2121 *2181 *2241 *2301 *2361 *2421 *2481 *2541 *2601 *2661 *2721 *2781 *2841 *2901 *2961 |}
== Month of Kanotomi (辛巳) == In the Gregorian calendar, during years ending in 0 or 5 (where the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|lt=Ten Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Heavenly Stems|qq=}} are {{ill|Kō (庚)|ja|庚|1=Kanoe (庚)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kō (庚)|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanoe (庚)|qq=}} or {{ill|Otsu (乙)|ja|乙|1=Kinoto (乙)|lt=Kinoto (乙)|2=ja|3=乙|4=zh|5=乙|1=Kinoto (乙)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Otsu (乙)|13=User:Immanuelle/Kinoto (乙)|qq=}}), the fourth month (April) is the Kanotomi month. Note that this can refer to the month in the {{ill|Lunisolar calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lunisolar calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}} or the “solar term” month (from {{ill|Rikka|ja|立夏|1=Lixia|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rikka|qq=}} to the day before {{ill|Bōshu|ja|芒種|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bōshu|qq=}}).
== Day of Kanotomi (辛巳) == A Kanotomi day is associated with the following selection day (選日).
=== Auspicious Days === On a Kanotomi day, it is the fourth day of {{ill|Small Earth|ja|犯土#小土|lt_ja=小土|lt=Shōdo|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Small Earth|qq=}}. == See Also == *{{prefix|qq=}} *{{intitle|qq=}}
